President Muhammadu Buhari, yesterday handed over Hajiya Fatima, daughter of Kano State governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje, to her groom. The president stood for the bride, while the National Leader of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu stood for the groom, Alhaji Idris Abiola Ajimobi. Senator Tinubu paid N50,000 dowry on behalf of the groom, who is also the son of the Oyo State governor, Alhaji Abiola Ajimobi. The marriage was contracted by the Emir of Kano, Malam Muhammad Sanusi ll, while the Chief Imam of Kano, Professor Sani Zaharaddeen, said special prayers for the couple. Daily Trust on Sunday observed that 22 governors, Senate President, Alhaji Abubakar Bukola Saraki and 11 ministers as well as the president’s Chief of Staff, Alhaji Abba Kyari, attended the wedding. The Chief Imam of Kano State, Professor Zaharaddeen, said the union between the children of the governors would promote unity among Hausa and Yoruba tribes. On his part, former governor of Kano State, Malam Ibrahim Shekarau, urged the groom and bride to always be patient with one another, saying, “patience is the key to a successful marriage”.